obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1447)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1447&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Coconut Development`
  line `Board Act, 1979.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 12th January, 1981, vide notification No. G.S.R. 13(E), dated 12th January, 1981, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1448)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1448&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient`
  line `in the public interest that the Union should take under its control the coconut industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1449)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1449&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) Board means the Coconut Development Board established under section 4;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) Chairman means the non-executive Chairman of the Board appointed under clause (a) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ba) Chief Executive Officer means the Chief Executive Officer of the Board appointed under sub-section (1) of section 7;]`
  line
  line `(c) coconut means the fruit of coconut palm and includes green coconut, ripe coconut and`
  line copra.
  line
  line `Explanation.--Coconut palm means the coconut tree, CocosNucifera Linn;`
  line
  line `(d) coconut industry does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) coir industry; or`
  line
  line `(ii) an industry from which products (including by-products) out of coconut oil are`
  line manufactured;
  line
  line `(e) member means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(f) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1450)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment and constitution of the Board`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1450&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette appoint in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, a Board to be called the Coconut Development Board.`
  line
  line `(2)The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3)The head office of the Board shall be at such place as the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `(4)The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) anon-executive Chairman, to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(aa) the Chief Executive Officer, to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ab) the Joint Secretary to the Government of India, in-charge of Mission for Integrated Development of Horticulture, ex officio ;]`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line ^2
  line `[the Horticulture Commissioner] to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c)the Director, Central Plantation Crops Research Institute (Indian Council of Agricultural`
  line `Research), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d)the Chairman of the Coir Board constituted under section 4 of the Coir Industry Act, 1953 (45`
  line `of 1953),ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e)three members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People and one`
  line `by the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(f)two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent respectively the`
  line `Ministries of the Central Government dealing with--`
  line
  line `(i)Revenue; and`
  line
  line `^3[(ii)Consumer Affairs;]`
  line
  line `^4[(g) four members to be appointed by the Central Government one each to represent the Governments of the States of Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala and Tamil Nadu, being States where coconut is grown on a large scale;`
  line
  line `(h) four members to be appointed by the Central Government by rotation in the alphabetical order to represent the States of Assam, Bihar, Chhattisgarh, Goa, Gujarat, Maharashtra, Nagaland, Odisha, Telengana, Tripura, West Bengal and the Union territories of Andaman and Nicobar Islands, Lakshadweep and Puducherry;`
  line
  line `(i) six members to be appointed by the Central Government, two to represent the coconut growers of the State of Kerala and one each to represent the coconut growers of the States of Andhra Pradesh, Gujarat Karnataka and Tamil Nadu;]`
  line
  line `(j)one member to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the coconut processing`
  line industry;
  line
  line `(k)two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent such other interests`
  line `connected with the coconut industry as, in the opinion of that Government, ought to be represented:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment under clauses (g) and (h) shall be made on there commendation`
  line `of the State Government or, as the case may be, of the Union territory concerned.`
  line
  line `(5)The Board shall elect, from amongst its members, a Vice-Chairman who shall exercise such of the`
  line `powers and perform such of the functions of the Chairman as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to`
  line `him by the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(6)The term of office of the members and the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure`
  line `to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7)Any officer of the Central Government, not being a member of the Board, when deputed by that`
  line `Government in this behalf, shall have the right to attend the meetings of the Board and take part in the`
  line `proceedings thereof but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(8)The Board may associate with itself in such manner, subject to such conditions and for such`
  line `purposes as may be prescribed, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the`
  line `discussions of the Board relevant to the purposes for which he has been associated but shall not have the`
  line `right to vote and shall be entitled to receive such allowances or fees as may be fixed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(9)No act or proceeding of the Board or any committee appointed by it under section9 shall be`
  line `invalidated merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a)any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board or such committee; or`
  line
  line `(b)any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board or such committee;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c)any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or such committee not affecting the merits of the`
  line case.
  line
  line `(10)The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard`
  line `to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided by`
  line `regulations made by the Board under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 3, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1987, s. 2, for the Agriculture Commissioner (w.e.f. 5-8-1987).`
  line
  line `3.Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 3, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clauses (g), (h) and (i) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1451)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Allowances payable to Chairman and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 4, for section 5 (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1451&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[5. Allowances payable to Chairman and members.--The Chairman and members of the Board`
  line `shall receive such allowances as may be fixed by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1452)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Resignation of members`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1452&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A member, other than an ex officio member, may resign his office by`
  line `giving notice thereof in writing to the Central Government and on such resignation being accepted, he`
  line `shall be deemed to have vacated his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1453)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Officers of the Board and other staff`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1453&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) There shall be a Chief Executive Officer of the Board, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India, to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(1A) The Chief Executive Officer shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(1B) The salaries and allowances payable to, and other conditions of service of, the Chief Executive Officer shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall appoint a Chief Coconut Development Officer to exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the ^2[Chief Executive Officer].`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Coconut Development Officer appointed under sub-section (2) shall have the right to`
  line `attend the meetings of the Board and its committees appointed under section 9 and take part in the`
  line `proceedings thereof but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall appoint a Secretary to the Board who shall exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such duties as may be prescribed or as may be delegated to him by the Board or the`
  line `Chairman ^3[or the Chief Executive Officer].`
  line
  line `(5) ^4[The Chief Executive Officer, the Chief Coconut Development Officer] and`
  line `allowances and shall be subject to such conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund`
  line `and other matters as may, from time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to such control and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Board may appoint such other`
  line `officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of its functions and the method`
  line `of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay and allowances of such other officers and`
  line `employees of the Board shall be such as may be provided by the Board by regulations made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(7) ^5[The Chief Executive Officer], the Chief Coconut Development Officer, the Secretary and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Board shall not undertake any work unconnected with their duties under this Act except`
  line `with the permission of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for “Chairman” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for “The Chief Coconut Development Officer” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `5.Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 5, for “the Chairman” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1454)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Special provision for transfer of employees to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1454&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the establishment of the`
  line `Board, it shall be lawful for the Central Government to transfer to the Board, by order, and with effect`
  line `from such date or dates as may be specified in the order, any officer or other employee holding office as`
  line `such in the Directorate of Coconut Development immediately before the date on which the Board is`
  line `established:`
  line
  line `Provided that the scale of pay of the post to which such officer or other employee is transferred shall`
  line `not be lower than the scale of pay of the post he was holding immediately before such transfer and the`
  line `other terms and conditions of service (including pension, leave, provident fund and medical benefits) of`
  line `the post to which he is transferred shall not be less favourable than the terms and conditions of service in`
  line `relation to the post held by him immediately before such transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if, immediately before the date of his transfer, any such officer or other`
  line `employee is officiating in a higher post under the Central Government either in a leave vacancy or in any`
  line `vacancy of specified duration, his pay and other allowances, if any, on transfer, shall be protected for the`
  line `unexpired period of such vacancy and thereafter he shall be entitled to the scale of pay applicable to the`
  line `post under the Central Government to which he would have reverted.`
  line
  line `(2) Before any order is issued under sub-section (1), all officers and other employees of the`
  line `Directorate of Coconut Development shall be give an option in such forms as may be prescribed, and`
  line `within such time as may be specified in that behalf by the Central Government, to express their`
  line `willingness or otherwise to become employees of the Board and such option once exercised shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under sub-section (1) shall be made in relation to any officer or other`
  line `employee of the Directorate of Coconut Development who has intimated his intention of not becoming an`
  line `employee of the Board within the time specified in that behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such of the persons employed by the Central Government in the said`
  line `Directorate, who do not express, within the time specified in that behalf, their intention of becoming the`
  line `employees of the Board, shall be dealt with in the same manner and in accordance with the same rules as`
  line `would apply to the employees of the Central Government in the event of the reduction of the strength of`
  line `the Department in which such persons have been employed.`
  line
  line `(3) An officer or other employee transferred by an order made under sub-section (1) shall, on and`
  line `from the date of transfer, cease to be an employee of the Central Government and become an officer or`
  line `other employee of the Board with such designation as the Board may determine and shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of the first and second provisos to sub-section (1), be governed by the regulations made by the`
  line `Board under this Act in respect of remuneration and other conditions of service (including pension, leave,`
  line `provident fund and medical benefits) and shall continue to be an officer or other employee of the Board`
  line `unless and until his employment is duly terminated by the Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time as the regulations referred to above governing the conditions of service of`
  line `its officers or other employees are framed by the Board, the relevant rules and orders framed by the`
  line `Central Government shall continue to be applicable to such officers or other employees.`
  line
  line `(4) If a question arises whether the terms and conditions of service prescribed in the regulations`
  line `framed by the Board in respect of any matter, including remuneration, pension, leave, provident fund and`
  line `medical benefits, are less favourable than those attached to the post held by an officer or other employee`
  line `immediately before his transfer to the Board, the decision of the Central Government in the matter shall`
  line `be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1455)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Committees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1455&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may appoint such committees as may be necessary for`
  line `the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall have the power to co-opt as members of any committee appointed under subsection`
  line `(1) such number of persons who are not members of the Board as it may think fit and the persons`
  line `so co-opted shall have the right to attend meetings of the committee and take part in its proceedings but`
  line `shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons co-opted as member of a committee under sub-section (2) shall be entitled to receive`
  line `such allowances or fees for attending meetings of the committee as may be fixed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1456)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1456&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the Board to promote, by such measures as it`
  line `thinks fit, the development under the control of the Central Government of the coconut industry.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the measures referred to`
  line `therein may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) adopting measures for the development of coconut industry so that farmers, particularly small`
  line `farmers, may become participants in, and beneficiaries of, the development and growth of coconut`
  line industry;
  line
  line `(b) recommending measures for improving the marketing of coconut and its products^1[within or outside India];`
  line
  line `(c) imparting technical advice to any person who is engaged in the cultivation of coconut or the`
  line `processing or marketing of coconut and its products;`
  line
  line `(d) providing financial or other assistance for the development of high yielding coconut hybrids,`
  line `adoption of improved methods of cultivation of coconut, modern technology for processing of`
  line `coconut and extension of areas under coconut cultivation (including replanting) with a view to`
  line `improving the growth of coconut industry;`
  line
  line `(e) adopting such measures as may be practicable for assisting coconut growers to get incentive`
  line `prices including recommending as and when necessary, minimum and maximum prices for coconut`
  line `and its products;`
  line
  line `(f) recommending measures for regulating import and export of coconut and its products;`
  line
  line `(g) collecting statistics from growers of coconut, dealers in coconut, manufacturers of coconut`
  line `products and such other persons and institutions as may be prescribed, on any matter relating to`
  line `coconut industry and publishing the statistics so collected or portions thereof or extracts therefrom;`
  line
  line `(h) fixing grades, specifications and standards for coconut and its products;`
  line
  line `(i) financing suitable schemes in consultation with the Central Government and the Governments`
  line `of the States where coconut is grown ^2***, so as to increase the production of coconut and`
  line `to improve its quality and yield; and for this purpose evolving schemes for award of prizes or grant of`
  line `incentives to growers of coconut and the manufacturers of its products and for providing marketing`
  line `facilities for coconut and its products;`
  line
  line `(j) assisting, encouraging, promoting or financing agricultural, technological, industrial or`
  line `economic research on coconut and its products in such manner as the Board may deem fit by making`
  line `use of available institutions;`
  line
  line `(k) undertaking such publicity and publishing such periodicals, books or bulletins, on the research`
  line `and development of coconut and its products, as may be found necessary;`
  line
  line `(l) setting up of regional offices and other agencies for the promotion and development of`
  line `production, grading and marketing of coconut and its products in coconut growing States and Union`
  line `territories for the efficient discharge of the functions and objectives of the Board;`
  line
  line `(m) such other measures as may, having regard to the purposes of this Act, be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Governments of the States where coconut is grown on a`
  line `large scale;`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall perform its functions under this section in accordance with, and subject to, such`
  line `rules as may be made by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 6, for “in India” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `2.The words “on a large scale” omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1457)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Dissolution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1457&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette and for reasons to be specified therein, direct that the Board shall be dissolved from such date and`
  line `for such period as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Board to make representations against the proposed dissolution and shall consider the`
  line `representations, if any, of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Board is dissolved under the provisions of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) all members, notwithstanding that their term of office has not expired, shall, from the date of`
  line `dissolution, vacate their offices as such member;`
  line
  line `(b) all powers and duties of the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may appoint in this behalf and their`
  line `remuneration shall be such as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) all funds and other properties vested in the Board shall, during the period of dissolution, vest`
  line `in the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(d) as soon as the period of dissolution expires, the Board shall be reconstituted in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1458)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1458&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made my Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Board by way of grants or loans such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1459)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Constitution of Coconut Development Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 4 of 1987, s. 10 (w.e.f. 21-3-1987).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1459&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be formed a Fund to be called`
  line `the Coconut Development Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) any grants or loans granted by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any grants or loans that may be made by any person for the purposes of this Act including`
  line `loans under section 14;`
  line
  line `(d) any grants or donations from State Governments, voluntary organisations or other institutions:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such grant, loan or donation shall be credited to the Fund except with prior approval`
  line `of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the cost of the measures referred to in section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and`
  line `other employees, as the case may be, of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) for meeting the other administrative expenses of the Board and any other expenses authorised`
  line `by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) for repayment of any loans.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1460)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Borrowing powers of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1460&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, for the purposes of carrying out its`
  line `functions under this Act, and with the previous approval of, and subject to the directions of the Central`
  line `Government, borrow money from--`
  line
  line `(a) the public by the issue or sale of bonds or debentures or both, carrying interest at such rates as`
  line `may be specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) any bank or other institution;`
  line
  line `(c) such other authority, organisation or institution as may be approved by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may guarantee the repayment of the monies borrowed by the Board`
  line `under sub-section (1) and the payment of interest thereon and other incidental charges.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1461)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `. Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1461&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts, in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Controller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Controller and Auditor-General of India at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by his and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of`
  line `the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1462)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1462&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall carry out such directions as may be`
  line `issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1463)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1463&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall furnish to the Central Government at such time and`
  line `in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such returns and`
  line `statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or existing programme for the promotion and`
  line `development of the coconut industry, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall furnish a programme of its activities for each financial year to the Central`
  line `Government for their information and directions, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall, as soon as possible, after`
  line `the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form and before such`
  line `date, as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and programmes during`
  line `the previous financial year.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the report received under sub-section (3) shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1464)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1464&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, or the Board or any committee appointed by it, or any member of the`
  line `Board or such committee, or any officer or other employee of the Central Government or of the Board or`
  line `any other person authorised by the Central Government or the Board, for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1465)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2021, s. 7, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1465&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the powers which may be exercised and functions which may be performed by the ViceChairman`
  line `of the Board under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of the members, the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure`
  line `to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, the members, under sub-section (6) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which and the purposes for which any person may be associated by the Board`
  line `under sub-section (8) of section 4;`
  line
  line `^1[(d) the powers to be exercised and the duties to be performed by the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (1A) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(da) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other conditions of service of, the Chief Executive Officer under sub-section (1B) of section 7;]`
  line
  line `(e) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which may be performed by the Chief`
  line `Coconut Development Officer of the Board under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(f) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which may be performed by the Secretary`
  line `of the Board under sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(g) the control and restrictions subject which officers and other employees may be appointed by`
  line `the Board under sub-section (6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which option may be given by the officers and other employees of the Directorate`
  line `of Coconut Development under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(i) the collection of statistics in respect of any matter relating to coconut industry under clause (g)`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(j) the matters in respect of which the Board may undertake measures in the discharge of its`
  line `functions under clause(m) of sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(k) the remuneration and other allowances payable to the person or persons referred to in clause`
  line `(b) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(l) the form in which the accounts of the Board shall be maintained under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and manner in which and the time at which the Board may furnish returns and`
  line `reports to the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which and the date before which the Board shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government the report of its activities and programmes under sub-section (3) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(o) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed by rules under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1466)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1466&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of this Act and the rules made thereunder, to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or`
  line `expedient for the purposes of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places at which meetings of the Board or any committee thereof, shall be held`
  line `and the procedure to be followed thereat, and the number of members which shall form a quorum at a`
  line `meeting under sub-section (10) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the method of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay and allowances of`
  line `any of the officers and other employees of the Board under sub-section(6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) generally, for the efficient conduct of the affairs of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, modify or rescind any`
  line `regulation sanctioned by it and the regulation so modified or rescinded shall have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however, that any such modification or rescission`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything done under the regulation before its modification or`
  line rescission.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1467)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216&sectionId=1467&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00005_197905_1517807325216
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, as`
  line `the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation, as the case may be, should not be made,`
  line `the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
